<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story -->
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title"><strong>UBER VALUED AT $62.5 BILLION </strong> <span class="divider"> | </span></span> Uber is close to completing another round of <b>fund-raising worth $2.1 billion</b>, according to people briefed on the companyâs plans,<br />
<a href="//www.nytimes.com/2015/12/04/business/dealbook/uber-nears-investment-at-a-62-5-billion-valuation.html?ref=dealbook">Mike Isaac and Leslie Picker report in DealBook.</a><br />
This round of venture capital, the companyâs single largest to date, would value the company at $62.5 billion and make it the worldâs most valuable private start-up. </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Tiger Global Management and T. Rowe Price both participated in the newest round, which <a href="//www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-12-03/uber-raises-funding-at-62-5-valuation">Bloomberg News reported</a> on Thursday. <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2015/10/24/business/dealbook/uber-said-to-plan-another-1-billion-in-fund-raising.html">The New York Times</a> had reported on the funding plans in October. </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Competition has intensified in the ride-hailing market.</b> Lyft is in talks to raise a further $500 million, which could value the company at about $4 billion. Didi Kuaidi has raised more than $4 billion in private investment to date. </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Tiger Global has also invested in Ola and GrabTaxi, which compete with Uber in India and Southeast Asia. This could be the first time a major institutional investor has <b>participated in fund-raising at both Uber and its major competitors</b>. Ola and GrabTaxi have formed a <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2015/12/04/technology/lyft-joins-with-asian-rivals-to-compete-with-uber.html?ref=dealbook">strategic partnership</a> with Lyft, which competes with Uber in the United States. </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Uber is <b>spending heavily to establish itself against its Asian competitors</b> and has allocated at least $1 billion to efforts to expand in China.</p>
</div>
